---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Madagascar Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/madagascar/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Mauritius for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/mauritius' },
  { title: 'South Africa for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/south-africa' },
  { title: 'France for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/france' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'madagascarFit', header: 'Madagascar Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'MGA$2.25M-3.21M/mo', madagascarFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'MGA$2.63M-3.76M/mo', madagascarFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'MGA$2.02M-2.89M/mo', madagascarFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'MGA$1.88M-2.69M/mo', madagascarFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Local/CFE', entryAge: 'Varies', renewal: 'Annual', monthlyFrom: 'MGA$400K-1M/mo', madagascarFit: 'Limited' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'MGA$2.02M-3.21M', annual: 'MGA$24.2M-38.5M' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'MGA$2.77M-4.28M', annual: 'MGA$33.2M-51.4M' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'MGA$3.73M-5.75M', annual: 'MGA$44.7M-69M' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Visit', monthly: 'MGA$100K-300K/visit', annual: 'Affordable' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Stay', monthly: 'MGA$500K-1.5M/day', annual: 'Per incident' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Madagascar 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Madagascar. Unique wildlife, French language, beaches, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Madagascar"
  subheadline="Madagascar offers unique wildlife found nowhere else, French language accessibility, beautiful beaches, and affordable living—an island of biodiversity for nature-loving retirees."
  heroImage="/images/countries/madagascar-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Madagascar</h2>
  <p>
    Madagascar offers lemurs and wildlife found nowhere else on Earth, French language accessibility, beautiful beaches, and affordable living. For nature-loving French-speaking retirees seeking unique biodiversity, Madagascar provides extraordinary experience at modest cost.
  </p>

  <p>
    Antananarivo (Tana) is the capital with best healthcare. Nosy Be offers beach resort lifestyle. Diego Suarez has northern beaches. Sainte-Marie is tropical island retreat. Most expats choose Tana or Nosy Be; healthcare very limited outside capital.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Very limited; evacuation to Réunion/France common</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Malagasy and French (official)</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> MGA$4M-8M/month (~$900-1,800 USD); affordable</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Tropical; varied by region</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Unique wildlife; Franco-Malagasy; isolated</li>
      <li><strong>Réunion access:</strong> French territory with EU healthcare 2 hours away</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Madagascar Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Madagascar healthcare is very limited—Clinique des Sœurs and private clinics in Tana provide basic care. Public system severely underfunded. Most complex cases evacuate to Réunion (French overseas territory, 2-hour flight) or South Africa. International insurance with evacuation essential.
  </p>

  <p>
    Healthcare outside Tana is very basic. Remote areas have minimal facilities. Réunion provides French/EU-standard healthcare nearby. International insurance with comprehensive evacuation coverage non-negotiable.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Réunion/France Backup Essential</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Healthcare in Madagascar is severely limited. Réunion (French overseas territory) is 2-hour flight with French healthcare standards. Include Réunion and France in coverage. This is not where to economize—evacuation coverage is essential.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Madagascar has accessible visa options:
  </p>

  <h3>Tourist Visa</h3>
  <p>
    30-90 days available on arrival or e-visa. Extensions possible.
  </p>

  <h3>Long-Stay Visa</h3>
  <p>
    For stays over 90 days. Various categories. Apply through embassy.
  </p>

  <h3>Transformable Visa</h3>
  <p>
    Can be converted to residence permit after arrival. Allows extended stay.
  </p>

  <h3>Residence Permit</h3>
  <p>
    For permanent settlement. Various categories including retirement.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Madagascar:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Entry:</strong> Travel insurance strongly recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Residence:</strong> Health insurance essential</li>
    <li><strong>Practical:</strong> International coverage absolutely essential</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> Réunion/France coverage critical</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Madagascar</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance with strong Réunion/France evacuation coverage essential. CFE (French expat insurance) option for French citizens. Local care handles only basic needs. Don't economize—healthcare limitations are severe.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Madagascar, comprehensive evacuation coverage critical:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Madagascar</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong global network, French territories</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive</li>
    <li><strong>CFE:</strong> French social security option for French citizens</li>
    <li><strong>Réunion access:</strong> French healthcare nearby</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage with comprehensive evacuation.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Madagascar (MGA ~4,500 to USD):
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Tana base:</strong> Best local healthcare</li>
    <li><strong>Don't cut evacuation:</strong> This is essential</li>
    <li><strong>CFE option:</strong> For French citizens</li>
    <li><strong>Preventive care:</strong> Stay healthy</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: French Wildlife Enthusiast, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> €2,200/month pension. Long-stay visa. Tana base.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> CFE + Cigna Global complement.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~MGA$2.5M/month (~$555). French system; Réunion backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: Nosy Be Beach Retiree, 70</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $2,800/month income. Residence permit. Island life.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global with maximum evacuation.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~MGA$3.2M/month (~$710). Remote island; comprehensive backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Conservation Worker, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $2,400/month income. Long-stay visa. Mobile lifestyle.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Allianz Care with comprehensive coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~MGA$2.1M/month (~$465). Wildlife work; evacuation essential.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Madagascar healthcare really that limited?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes—Madagascar is one of world's poorest countries. Healthcare severely underfunded. Basic care available in Tana; anything complex needs evacuation. Réunion (French territory) is 2-hour flight with proper hospitals. Evacuation coverage essential.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Do I need French?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Essential—French is official language alongside Malagasy. Healthcare, administration, business in French. English very limited. French speakers have significant advantage. Learning French important for Madagascar life.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Madagascar safe?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Generally safe—low violent crime. Petty theft exists. Political instability occasionally. Tourist areas well-managed. Remote areas require planning. Normal precautions apply. Overall safer than reputation suggests.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What's unique about Madagascar wildlife?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Extraordinary—90% of wildlife found nowhere else on Earth. Lemurs, chameleons, baobabs, fossa. Island isolation created unique evolution. Multiple national parks. Conservation important. Wildlife is primary attraction.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers for Madagascar coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Madagascar authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
